'''Plumbworld''' is a specialist bathroom retailer based in the market town of [[Evesham]] in the [[United Kingdom]]. The company was founded by the current CEO James Hickman in 1999 and operates exclusively online. It was owned by the [[Grafton Group]] between 2006 and 2019, now back under the control of the original founder after a management buyout.

== History ==

Plumbworld was founded in 1999 by James and Anita Hickman. The company grew into a multi-million pound business within a matter of years. In 2006, James Hickman sold the company to the UK and Irish based company [[Grafton Group]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The History of Grafton Group|url=http://www.graftonplc.com/about-us/our-heritage|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

In 2008, Plumbworld entered the [[power tools]] market for the first time with a new e-commerce website trading by the name of Toolbox.co.uk.<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld founder launches power tool website|url=http://www.diyweek.net/news/news.asp?id=11090|publisher=DIY WEEK|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

2010 announced the launch of further e-commerce website this time specialising in [[barbecues]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld launch new E-Commerce website specialising in BBQ's products|url=http://www.applegate.co.uk/b2b-news/articles/plumbworld-launch-commerce-website-specialising-bbqs-products-25995.html|publisher=Applegate|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> and [[wood burning stoves]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld Expand Empire in Wood Burning Stoves Website Launch|url=http://www.techzone360.com/news/2010/09/12/5002002.htm|publisher=Tech Zone 360|accessdate=28 April 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429045723/http://www.techzone360.com/news/2010/09/12/5002002.htm|archivedate=29 April 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

In 2012 and because of ventures into various sectors in the home and garden markets, Plumbworld rebranded to Online Home Retail but continued to trade as normal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld Ltd is Now Online Home Retail Limited|url=http://www.benzinga.com/pressreleases/12/05/p2621398/rebrand-plumbworld-ltd-is-now-online-home-retail-limited}}</ref>

2014 saw Plumbworld venture into the world of television for the first time with the 'We Love to Say No' advert developed by The Market Creative. The project encompassed a 30-second [[TV advert]] as well as a direct marketing campaign to help with the re-branding and new website for the company.<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld Ventures into TV Advertising|url=http://www.themarketcreative.com/our-work/plumbworld/|publisher=The Market Creative|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

== Current ==

In January 2019 a team led by the founder of the business James Hickman bought back the company from Grafton Group plc, a listed builders merchant.<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld Bought Back From Grafton Group|url=http://www.kbbreview.com/20425/topstory/plumbworld-bought-back-from-grafton-group/|publisher=KBBReview|accessdate=17 April 2019}}</ref>

== Awards ==

The company has been recognised nationwide and has claimed various awards over the years including the prestigious 'Top Ten Website' by Hitwise.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bathroom Retailer, Plumbworld, Scoops Two Awards|url=http://www.pr.com/press-release/40826|publisher=PR.Com|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

== Charitable Activities ==

The business has been involved in numerous charitable activities since being founded in 1999 and continues to raise money on a daily basis. Over the years Plumbworld have been involved in raising money for [[Sport Relief]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Plumbworld Staff Raises Money for Sport Reliefs|url=http://www.zoominfo.com/p/Gary-Hopkins/1414725242}}</ref> Evesham's historic Regal Cinema relaunch,<ref>{{cite web|title=E-Commerce Giant Plumbworld Help With Evesham’s Historic Regal Cinema Re-Launch|url=http://digitaljournal.com/pr/555554|publisher=Digital Journal|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> and various nationwide community projects.<ref>{{cite web|title=Help In The London Community Aided By The Plumbworld Team|url=http://digitaljournal.com/pr/454674|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> Plumbworld joined forces with The Heart of England Forest Project in order to plant more than one million trees.<ref>{{cite web|title=Heart of England Forest Millionth Tree Planting|url=http://www.heartofenglandforest.com/uncategorized/heart-of-england-forest-millionth-tree-planting|accessdate=28 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016102928/http://www.heartofenglandforest.com/uncategorized/heart-of-england-forest-millionth-tree-planting|archive-date=16 October 2013|dead-url=yes}}</ref> The ongoing partnership saw 9.11 hectares being used to plant nearly 10,000 trees and the same again the following year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tree Planting in the Online Home Retail Wood|url=http://www.heartofenglandforest.com/corporate-social-responsibility/csr-tree-planting-in-the-online-home-retail-wood|publisher=Heart of England Forest|accessdate=28 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016085217/http://www.heartofenglandforest.com/corporate-social-responsibility/csr-tree-planting-in-the-online-home-retail-wood|archive-date=16 October 2013|dead-url=yes}}</ref> The company have always taken responsibilities to the environment seriously and continues to support this important project.<ref>{{cite web|title=Plant a Tree with Plumbworld!|url=https://www.plumbworld.co.uk/plant-a-tree-with-plumbworld-infopage|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

